when you pay attention to it, a large part of our social bubble (entertainment, social media, consumer goods, etc) is centered around downplaying large societal problems or presenting us with pseudo-solutions that make us feel good.

maybe this is due to well-off people in the imperial core being insulated from political strife and social instability to the point of conceiving of "political" problems and "personal" problems as two entirely separate things that never intersect

one thing thats becoming more obvious about big, earth-scale threats, like climate change or nuclear war or covid, is that people conceive of the threat as fundamentally all-or-nothing. either it kills literally every single human being currently alive, or it doesnt matter at all
